# PostgreSQL Standards

## NEVER write a query without org_id in the WHERE clause

Every table in `ibex_core` has `org_id`. RLS is the database-level defence. The application layer is the second defence. Both must be present.

```sql
-- WRONG — no org_id; RLS is the only protection
SELECT * FROM ibex_core.agents WHERE id = $1;

-- WRONG — RLS provides isolation but this allows timing attacks
-- (response time differs when row exists vs not)
SELECT id FROM ibex_core.agents WHERE id = $1 AND org_id = $2;

-- RIGHT — explicit org_id AND deleted_at guard; always limit columns
SELECT id, org_id, status, slug
FROM ibex_core.agents
WHERE id      = $1
  AND org_id  = $2
  AND deleted_at IS NULL
LIMIT 1;
```

```go
// In Go store code — org_id must be a bound parameter, never interpolated
const q = `
    SELECT id, org_id, status
    FROM ibex_core.agents
    WHERE id     = $1
      AND org_id = $2
      AND deleted_at IS NULL
    LIMIT 1`

row := pool.QueryRow(ctx, q, agentID, orgID) // both are parameters
```

## SET LOCAL before every transaction that touches RLS tables

```go
// RLS reads current_setting('app.current_org_id').
// Set it at the start of every transaction.
func withOrgContext(ctx context.Context, pool *pgxpool.Pool, orgID uuid.UUID, fn func(pgx.Tx) error) error {
    return pgx.BeginTxFunc(ctx, pool, pgx.TxOptions{}, func(tx pgx.Tx) error {
        if _, err := tx.Exec(ctx,
            "SET LOCAL app.current_org_id = $1", orgID.String(),
        ); err != nil {
            return fmt.Errorf("set org context: %w", err)
        }
        return fn(tx)
    })
}
```

## No SELECT * in application queries

```sql
-- WRONG — fetches all columns including future-added sensitive columns
SELECT * FROM ibex_core.tokens WHERE id = $1;

-- RIGHT — explicit columns; adding a sensitive column doesn't leak it
SELECT id, org_id, type, prefix, name, permissions, expires_at, is_revoked, last_used_at
FROM ibex_core.tokens
WHERE id = $1 AND is_revoked = FALSE;
```

## Index every foreign key and every filtering column

```sql
-- Every org_id column is indexed with a partial index WHERE deleted_at IS NULL.
-- Every (org_id, status) pair used in WHERE clauses is a composite index.
-- Every column used in ORDER BY without a WHERE equality is indexed.

-- Required indexes for any new table:
CREATE INDEX idx_{table}_org_id ON ibex_core.{table}(org_id) WHERE deleted_at IS NULL;
-- Add more specific indexes as query patterns require.
```

## Soft deletes — set deleted_at, never DELETE rows on business entities

```sql
-- WRONG — hard delete loses audit trail
DELETE FROM ibex_core.agents WHERE id = $1;

-- RIGHT — soft delete
UPDATE ibex_core.agents
SET deleted_at = NOW()
WHERE id     = $1
  AND org_id = $2
  AND deleted_at IS NULL;
```

## Timestamps — always TIMESTAMPTZ, never TIMESTAMP

```sql
-- WRONG — stores without timezone; ambiguous on DST transitions
created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()

-- RIGHT — always with timezone (UTC internally, any TZ in client)
created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
```

## N+1 query prevention

```go
// WRONG — queries inside loop
agents, _ := store.ListAgents(ctx, orgID)
for _, agent := range agents {
    stats, _ := store.GetStats(ctx, agent.ID) // N+1!
    render(agent, stats)
}

// RIGHT — single join or batch lookup
type AgentWithStats struct { Agent; Stats }
agentsWithStats, _ := store.ListAgentsWithStats(ctx, orgID)
for _, item := range agentsWithStats {
    render(item.Agent, item.Stats)
}
```
